🎥: @alphafoodie ⁣
4 ingredients to heaven 😍⁣
⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(For 16 Servings)⁣
4 avocado* medium-sized⁣
1 cup pistachios⁣
1 cup coconut cream⁣
2 tBsp honey⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Blitz the pistachios in a blender/food processor to obtain a flour-like consistency.⁣
2. Open up the avocados, scoop out the flesh & add it to the pistachio flour.⁣
3. Add the coconut cream and honey to the pistachios and avocados and blend them well until you obtain a creamy mixture.⁣
4. Serve in cups or the avocado shells and put in the freezer. Keep for at least 30-60 minutes so the cream can begin to properly set.⁣
5. If completely frozen, let it out of the freezer for about 30 minutes so it softens.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy🌱😋⁣
⁣

⁣ ⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(For 4 servings)⁣
1 tbsp olive oil⁣
½ onion, small diced⁣
2 garlic cloves, minced⁣
2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved⁣
8 oz fresh mozzarella pearls⁣
¾ tsp salt⁣
¼ tsp pepper⁣
2 bell peppers ⁣
½ cup balsamic vinegar⁣
Handful basil leaves, thinly sliced⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat oven to 375F(190C).⁣
2. Pour olive oil in a small skillet and place over medium-low heat. Saute, onion and garlic stirring occasionally, until vegetables are softened and starting to brown slightly, about 5 minutes. ⁣
3. Transfer to a bowl and add the cherry tomatoes and mozzarella. Toss the mixture with the salt and pepper. Set aside.⁣
4. Slice the bell peppers in half and place cut-side down in a baking dish. Drizzle with a little olive oil and sprinkle with salt. Flip peppers over and fill with the tomato-mozzarella mixture. ⁣
5. Roast for about 15-20 minutes, or until edges of peppers begin to char.⁣
6. While peppers are roasting, make the balsamic reduction. Pour balsamic vinegar in a small pot. Heat until vinegar comes to a simmer. Lower the heat and reduce until vinegar becomes syrupy, about 7-10 minutes.⁣
7. Drizzle the peppers with balsamic reduction once baked. ⁣
8. Serve and enjoy⁣
⁣

Full recipe below, tag someone who would love this!⁣
⁣
Throw together this simple, fresh salad in 15 minutes flat for a colourful, speedy side dish😍⁣
⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(For 6 Servings)⁣
2 ears corn⁣
olive oil, for brushing⁣
8 oz dried orecchiette pasta(225 g), cooked according to package instructions⁣
2 cups cherry tomato(400 g)⁣
½ cup red onion(75 g), diced⁣
1 avocado, diced⁣
1 ½ cups fresh cilantro(60 g)⁣
⅓ cup olive oil(80 mL)⁣
3 tablespoons lime juice⁣
1 clove garlic, roughly chopped⁣
½ teaspoon chili powder⁣
2 teaspoons honey⁣
salt, to taste⁣
pepper, to taste⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Microwave the corn on a microwave-safe plate on high for 7 minutes. Remove from the microwave, and grip the corn with a dish towel. Then cut off the bottom end with a serrated knife. Slide the corn out of the husk.⁣
2. Brush the corn with olive oil, then place on a cast iron grill pan or outdoor grill over medium-high heat. Grill for 5-6 minutes on each side, until the kernels are slightly charred.⁣
3. Saw off the kernels with a serrated knife. The kernels will fall into the pan for easy collection.⁣
4. For the vinaigrette: Combine the cilantro, olive oil, lime juice, garlic, chili powder, honey, salt, and pepper in a food processor and blend until smooth.⁣
5. In a large bowl, add the pasta, corn, tomatoes, red onion, avocado, and vinaigrette, and mix until well-combined.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy🌱😋⁣
⁣

📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(For 4 Servings)⁣
3 oz instant ramen(85 g), 3 packages⁣
8 cups water(1.9 L), boiling hot⁣
1 clove garlic, minced⁣
1 teaspoon cornstarch⁣
2 tablespoons sesame oil⁣
1 lime, juiced⁣
¼ cup soy sauce(60 mL), plus 1 tablespoon⁣
2 cups broccoli floret(300 g)⁣
1 tablespoon olive oil, divided⁣
¾ lb flank steak(340 g), thinly sliced⁣
½ medium yellow onion, thinly sliced⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Place the ramen noodles in a large bowl and pour the boiling water over them. Let sit for 6 minutes, stirring every now and then. Drain and rinse under cold water. Set aside.⁣
2. In a small bowl, combine the garlic, cornstarch, sesame oil, lime juice, and soy sauce. Stir well, then set aside.⁣
3. Place the broccoli in a large, microwave-safe bowl and microwave for 1½ minutes, until soft. Set aside.⁣
4. Heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil in a large, nonstick pan over high heat. Add the steak to the pan and toss with 2 tablespoons of the reserved sauce. Cook until browned, about 2 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.⁣
5. Heat another teaspoon of olive oil in the pan, then add the onion. Cook, stirring often, until browned, about 4 minutes.⁣
6. Add the broccoli and cook until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.⁣
7. Add the remaining teaspoon of olive oil to the pan, then add the noodles and the remaining sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until the noodles soak up the sauce. Return the cooked vegetables and steak to the pan and stir to distribute.⁣
8. Transfer the noodles to a serving dish and garnish with green onions, cilantro, and sesame seeds, if using.⁣
9. Serve and enjoy🌱😋⁣

📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(For 6 servings)⁣
1 tbsp oil⁣
1 tbsp minced garlic, minced⁣
½ cup red onion(75 g), chopped⁣
1 cup bell pepper(100 g), chopped⁣
1 cup tomato(200 g), chopped⁣
3 cups water(720 mL)⁣
1 ½ cups rice(300 g)⁣
1 cup black beans(170 g)⁣
1 tbsp fresh cilantro, chopped⁣
1 cup tomato sauce(260 g)⁣
1 tsp chili powder⁣
1 tsp cumin⁣
1 tsp salt⁣
1 tsp pepper⁣
½ cup shredded cheese(50 g), optional⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat oven to 400F (200C).⁣
2. Put oil in a cast-iron skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and onion to skillet and stir until garlic is slightly golden and onion has softened.⁣
3. Add pepper and sauté 2-3 minutes or until peppers have softened then add tomatoes and sauté for a further minute.⁣
4. Remove sauteed vegetables and set aside then pour water into the skillet and wait for it to come to a boil.⁣
5. Add rice and stir for 12-15 minutes until rice is fluffier but still slightly tender.⁣
6. Make a circle in the center of the rice and add your sautéed vegetables and black beans to the skillet and mix.⁣
7. Add cilantro, tomato sauce, chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper, and stir.⁣

Honey Garlic Chicken w/ NOODOS 🥰

Via @denvafoodie

* 5 boneless, skinless chicken thighs
* 1 tbs of soy sauce 
* 2 tbs of oyster sauce 
* 1 tbs of honey 
* 1 tsp of garlic powder 
* 1/4 tsp of salt 
* 1/4 tsp of black pepper 
**Mix all together and let it marinate for at least 30 minutes. Cook it in the air fryer at 360 degrees for 20 mins. Flip halfway through. 

* 500g of spaghetti noodles (cooked and drained) 
* 4 minced garlic cloves 
* 1 inch knob of ginger (minced) 

Sauce 
* 1/4 cup of regular soy sauce
* 1 tsp of thick soy sauce 
* 3 tbs of oyster sauce 
* 2 tbs of honey 
* 2 tbs of sesame oil 
* 1 tsp of dried red pepper flakes 
**Mix all the above together in a bowl. 

1. In a large frying pan, heat up 3 tbs of oil. 
2. Add in your garlic and ginger for about 2-3 minutes on medium high heat. 
3. Add your spaghetti noodles.
4. Pour your sauce on top. Give it a good mix and cook for ~3 minutes.
5. Serve with your honey garlic chicken on top and garnish with chopped green onions.

Enjoy!!!!

Sesame Salmon, Baked Paprika Fingerling Potatoes and Caprese Salad from @healthymoodsf 😍 If this meal doesn’t scream of summer, I don’t know what does 😍 So freaking amazing! We’ve been so active outdoors with the nice weather and this learn protein, healthy meal refuels the fam for more fun!⠀
Potatoes:⠀
1 pound fingerling potatoes 1 tsp paprika⠀
1/4 tsp black pepper⠀
1/2 tsp garlic powder⠀
1/2 tsp salt⠀
1/4 tsp dill weed⠀
1 tsp dried Rosemary⠀
1 1/2 - 2 tbsp olive oil⠀
Directions:⠀
Cut the potatoes in fourths and toss them in oil and all the seasoning. Baked in my convection oven at 425 for 15 minutes.⠀
CAPRESE SALAD:⠀
Ingredients:⠀
2 small tomatoes⠀
4-5 slices fresh mozzarella⠀
Handful of fresh basil⠀
Salt+pepper⠀
Olive Oil⠀
Balsamic glaze or Balsamic Vinegar⠀
Directions:⠀
Slice tomatoes into rounds, and layer them with fresh mozzarella cheese and fresh basil. Drizzle with olive oil & balsamic Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.⠀

Eat or pass this Shrimp Pasta with Creamy Mozzarella Sauce? 👀💕 from @juliasalbumblog⠀
.⠀
8 oz penne pasta⠀
Shrimp:⠀
* 2 tablespoons olive⠀
* 1 pound shrimp⠀
* 3 garlic cloves minced⠀
* 1/4 teaspoon salt⠀
Creamy Sauce:⠀
* 4 oz sun-dried tomatoes (without oil)⠀
* 4 garlic cloves , minced⠀
* 1 cup half and half⠀
* 1 cup mozzarella cheese , shredded⠀
* 1 tablespoon dried basil⠀
* 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes , crushed⠀
* 1/8 teaspoon paprika⠀
* 1/2 cup reserved cooked pasta water⠀
* 1/4 teaspoon salt⠀
Cook pasta according to package instructions. Reserve some cooked pasta water. Drain the pasta.⠀
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add shrimp with minced garlic.  Cook the shrimp on one side for about 1 minute, until shrimp turns pink or golden brown on that side. While it cooks, sprinkle salt over the shrimp to cover every single shrimp. After 1 minute, Flip the shrimp over to the other side and cook for about 30 seconds or 1 minute more. The shrimp should be golden color or pink on both sides and not overcooked. Remove the shrimp to a plate, being careful to leave all the oil in the skillet.⠀
How to make creamy sauce To the same skillet, add sun-dried tomatoes and more minced garlic. Saute sun-dried tomatoes in olive oil (remaining from shrimp) on medium heat, stirring, for 1 minute until the garlic is fragrant. Add half and half to the 3. hot skillet with sun-dried tomatoes and bring to boil. Add shredded cheese to the skillet, and quickly stir in while boiling. Immediately reduce to simmer. Continue cooking the sauce on low simmer heat, constantly stirring, until all the cheese melts and the creamy sauce forms. Add basil, crushed red pepper flakes, paprika. Stir. Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt gradually, stirring on low heat. Add cooked pasta to the sauce, and reheat gently on medium heat. Add the cooked shrimp, stir it in. Let everything simmer on low heat for a couple of minutes for flavors to combine.

Crispy Garlic Herb Roasted Potatoes 🌱 by @cleanfoodcrush

Potatoes are a VERY welcome addition to any meal!

Who doesn't LOVE potatoes?!!! 

Whether it's a simple week night dinner or a big holiday meal, these crispy roasted potatoes will be much appreciated by all!

I love leaving the potato skins on for recipes such as this. The skin gives a lot more crunch and texture, not to mention the skin is full of nutrients!

For an added treat, you could lightly sprinkle your potatoes with parmesan cheese right when they come out of the oven.

6 servings 

Ingredients:
2 lbs new red potatoes
6 fresh garlic cloves, minced or pressed
3 Tbsps chopped fresh oregano
3 Tbsps chopped fresh rosemary
2 Tbsps chopped fresh chives, to garnish
2 Tbsps chopped fresh parsley, to garnish
3 Tbsps olive oil or avocado oil
¼ tsp pepper, or to taste
½ tsp sea salt, or to taste
sea salt flakes, to sprinkle before serving

Instructions:

Preheat your oven to 400 degrees f. and line a large baking tray with parchment paper.

Thoroughly wash and scrub the potatoes, then pat dry with paper towels, or allow to air dry.

With a very sharp knife, carefully chop them into bite sized cubes then transfer them onto the prepared baking tray.

I love to keep the skins on for these. 

In a small bowl whisk minced garlic, chopped oregano, chopped rosemary, oil, sea salt and pepper. 

Pour this herb mixture over potatoes and toss until very evenly coated, then arrange in a single layer without overlapping onto your sheet pan. They crisp up more if they are given space in the baking sheet.

Roast in your preheated oven, flipping them halfway through, until nice golden and crispy (about 35-45 minutes). Watch them and pull them out when they are to your liking.

Garnish with fresh chopped parsley, chives and sprinkle with additional sea salt flakes if desired.

Serve warm and enjoy!
